 theory, and finally to practice in the first detailed account of how Thompson's ideas laid the foundations for the cooperative movement, which is now the world's largest democratic social movement.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCooperation. 0aDemocracy. 0aHappiness. 0aUtilitarianism. 4aHistory : History. 4aPolitics and Law : Democracy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Economy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Theory. 4aSociology : Social Movements. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845205040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438452050423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438452050/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles